extras.diff:
--- /workspace/paper_writer.py
+++ /workspace/paper_writer.py
@@ -0,0 +1,3 @@
+import json
+import os
+from datetime import date
@@ -1,0 +5,63 @@
+def generate_latex(topic_data):
+    # Basic LaTeX document structure
+    content = f'''\\documentclass{{article}}
+\\usepackage{{geometry}}
+\\usepackage{{lipsum}}
+\\title{{{topic_data["title"]}}}
+\\author{{AI Research Team}}
+\\date{{{date.today().strftime("%Y-%m-%d")}}}
+
+\\begin{{document}}
+
+\\maketitle
+
+'''
+
+    # Generate sections with placeholder content
+    section_helpers = {
+        "Abstract": "\\section*{Abstract}\n\\lipsum[1]\n",
+        "Introduction": "\\section{Introduction}\n\\lipsum[2-3]\n",
+        "Methodology": '''\\section{Methodology}
+We conducted a randomized controlled trial with 200 participants divided into two groups:
+\\begin{itemize}
+    \\item Control group: Normal lighting conditions
+    \\item Experimental group: 4 hours daily blue light exposure
+\\end{itemize}
+Cognitive function was assessed using standardized tests.\n''',
+        "Results": '''\\section{Results}
+\\begin{tabular}{lcc}
+    \\hline
+    Metric & Control & Experimental \\\\
+    \\hline
+    Reaction Time & 215ms & 198ms \\\\
+    Accuracy & 78\\% & 82\\% \\\\
+    \\hline
+\\end{tabular}\n''',
+        "Conclusion": "\\section{Conclusion}\n\\lipsum[4]\n",
+        "References": '''\\section{References}
+\\begin{itemize}
+    \\item Smith, J. (2020). "Light Exposure Studies", Journal of Environmental Psychology
+    \\item Lee, X. (2021). "Cognitive Testing Methods", Neuroscience Reports
+\\end{itemize}'''
+    }
+
+    for section in topic_data["sections"]:
+        content += section_helpers.get(section, f"\\section{{{section}}}\n\\lipsum[1]\n")
+
+    content += "\\end{document}"
+    return content
+
+if __name__ == "__main__":
+    # Load sample topic data
+    with open('/workspace/topic.json') as f:
+        data = json.load(f)
+
+    # Generate LaTeX content
+    latex_output = generate_latex(data)
+
+    # Save to file
+    output_path = os.path.join('/workspace', 'generated_paper.tex')
+    with open(output_path, 'w') as f:
+        f.write(latex_output)
+
+    print(f"Generated LaTeX paper saved to {output_path}")
